h2. Preparing the Onboarding Data

Retrieving this data will require gathering data about org, company, competitor company, brand, and competitor brand.

The slack message should conform to the BrandOnboardingContextRequest at: [https://evolve24.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/bgp/pages/3091890181/Data+Sources+for+MarTech|https://evolve24.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/bgp/pages/3091890181/Data+Sources+for+MarTech|smart-link] 



The records will include one brand, and two competitor brands that are related to it

Here, we’ll go with a somewhat flat structure where the org_id/org_name are included in each record.



subcategory is included in the DB record for the brand/competitor brand’s parent – either a company or competitor company

category can be derived from category using a hard-coded map. The mappings are in the spreadsheet attached to this ticket. subcategory is the “subcategory” column, and category is the [GROOMING: “one_up” column?]

is_competitor will be true or false, depending on the record is for a competitor product brand or product brand.

{code:none}New onboarding request for brand [BRAND NAME] (id: [BRAND ID]):

[
    // one brand, with is_competitor=false
    {
         org_id: string;
         org_name: string;
         brand_id: string;
         brand_name: string;
         category: string;
         subcategory: string;
         is_competitor: boolean;
    },
    // ...two competitor brands, with is_competitor=true
]{code}



----

Separate ticket for the task of setting up the webhook

Let’s have a more detailed follow-up discussion on whether to store status on brands or have a separate context/job table related to brands to store them.

Probably want to know who triggered this and when (auditing)

This will have implications for other tickets related to brand/status if we have another table, so be sure to update those.

