* Endpoint accepts and processes a list of topic IDs to associate with a brand
* Updates the brand_topic table with the new topic relationships
* Sets the brand proximity value for each topic-brand relationship
* Updates the active status of topics for the brand
* Returns an appropriate 204 (No Content) response on success
* Returns appropriate error responses for invalid requests (400) or if brand does not exist (404)
* Works as expected when a topic is being added to a brand for the first time
* Works as expected when a topic's relationship to a brand is being updated
* Properly enforces security through authenticated requests

*Request*

{{PUT /brand/{brandId}/topic}}

{code:json}{
  "topicIds": ["string"]
}{code}

*Response*

{{204 No Content}}

